The paper discusses the use of technology-based interventions for individuals with autism spectrum disorder, which involves the intersection of computer science, psychology, and neuroscience. The methodologies reviewed include computer aided systems, computer vision assisted technologies, and virtual reality or artificial intelligence-assisted interventions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
